<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Mid2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Mid,</orth> adj. middle: <cit><quote>past the m. season,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.239" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 239</bibl></cit> (noon). <cit><quote>m. age and wrinkled eld,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.104" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 104</bibl></cit> (i. e. the prime of life; cf. <bibl n="shak. son 7.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 7, 6</bibl>). In <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.8.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 8, 64</bibl> F<hi rend="sub">1. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.8.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 8, 64</bibl> 3</hi> <emph>through the very middest of you;</emph> F<hi rend="sub">4</hi> and most M. Edd. <emph>midst.</emph>
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>